# zget: The Webport Pivot & MCP Integration

Successfully transitioned [zget](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget) into a high-fidelity media archival ecosystem with a headless engine, a premium PWA frontend, and a production-ready MCP server.

## Key Accomplishments

### 1. Headless Archival Server (`zget-server`)
- Implemented a robust **FastAPI** backend that manages the [DownloadQueue](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/queue/manager.py#63-331) and SQLite library independently of the UI.
- Added `/api/media/{id}` route for direct streaming and downloading to mobile devices (Camera Roll support).
- Launched using `uv run` to ensure all high-fidelity dependencies (`yt-dlp`, etc.) are correctly managed.

### 2. Premium Webport (PWA)
- **Aesthetic Integration**: Adopted the **StoryTime** "bioluminescent" palette (Gold/Void), 16-bit pixel typography (`Press Start 2P`), and subtle CRT scanlines.
- **Mobile-Native Features**:
  - **Share Sheet Support**: Integrated the Web Share Target API so you can share URLs directly to [zget](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget).
  - **Auto-Install**: PWA manifest and service worker included for "Add to Home Screen" support.
  - **Glassmorphism UI**: High-fidelity dashboard with real-time progress bars and library sync.

### 3. MCP Server & Agent Integration
- Exposed 9 high-fidelity tools including `zget_download`, `zget_search`, and `zget_extract_info`.
- Verified interoperability with Antigravity agents (e.g., Librarian).

